1
00:00:05,740 --> 00:00:10,810
Sometimes it says 
Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī worships Sūrya.

2
00:00:10,810 --> 00:00:14,509
[Ultimate Nectar Extraction]

3
00:00:15,171 --> 00:00:28,228
The famous yoga mantras mention,
Guru Mahārāj said, Nārāyaṇ.

4
00:00:28,228 --> 00:00:31,931
He quoted, and I don't have it
committed to memory,

5
00:00:31,931 --> 00:00:36,606
He's the light of the light.

6
00:00:36,606 --> 00:00:45,680
When you look at the sun, it's divine
illumination, actually—we know that.

7
00:00:45,680 --> 00:00:51,895
It's divine. Sun-light is divine.
It's obvious.

8
00:00:51,949 --> 00:00:55,415
Every morning it's divine light.

9
00:00:55,415 --> 00:01:04,110
Nārāyaṇ is in the centre of the sun;
the light of the light.

10
00:01:04,252 --> 00:01:08,799
That's how Guru Mahārāj described.

11
00:01:09,122 --> 00:01:18,490
So if we're fortunate to
give some appreciation and go deeper …

12
00:01:18,490 --> 00:01:19,628
Sometimes Guru Mahārāj ...

13
00:01:19,628 --> 00:01:27,216
Śri Puram means the city of Her
… that She's illuminating.

14
00:01:27,216 --> 00:01:33,311
The heart of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī
is illuminating the whole spiritual existence,

15
00:01:33,311 --> 00:01:37,853
and revealing Kṛṣṇa.

16
00:01:38,053 --> 00:01:49,442
By the light of the sun we can see
the Ghanaśyām; Śyāmasundar.

17
00:01:49,507 --> 00:02:00,044
Like this afternoon's clouds here are
Ghanaśyām-like clouds, revealed by sunlight.

18
00:02:00,121 --> 00:02:09,277
There, Kṛṣṇa's steps are very soft
and short. He's a cowherd boy.

19
00:02:09,446 --> 00:02:17,978
Adbhuta-kram: 'He of wonderful stride
and wonderful step.'

20
00:02:22,746 --> 00:02:26,849
Divine movement.

21
00:02:27,172 --> 00:02:32,548
Movement enhanced with beauty is dance.

22
00:02:32,617 --> 00:02:40,802
The Kṛṣṇa movement is movement
enhanced with beauty; dance.

23
00:02:40,949 --> 00:02:46,848
The Kṛṣṇa movement is
the most beautiful movement,

24
00:02:47,493 --> 00:02:53,033
other than 'that Kṛṣṇa'.

25
00:02:53,673 --> 00:03:00,562
Gāndharvikā—Gāndharvā Govindasundar—
Srila Guru Mahārāj's deity, Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī,

26
00:03:00,562 --> 00:03:10,938
she's dancing and singing, attracting
the centre of all attraction; Kṛṣṇa.

27
00:03:11,088 --> 00:03:13,534
Kṛṣ-ṇa.

28
00:03:13,688 --> 00:03:18,420
'Attracting', kṛṣir bhū-vācakaḥ śabdo (Cc: 2.9.30).

29
00:03:18,696 --> 00:03:21,150
Kṛṣṇa, 'attracting everyone
to the centre,

30
00:03:21,150 --> 00:03:24,963
with His irresistible charm,
beauty and sweetness';

31
00:03:24,963 --> 00:03:28,511
Kṛṣ-ṇa, 'and then nourishing everyone'.

32
00:03:28,511 --> 00:03:34,128
Hlādinī-śakti puṣṭi karan:
Rādhārāṇī, extracting …

33
00:03:34,128 --> 00:03:39,602
It's great that Kṛṣṇa 
is Akhila-rasāmṛta-mūrti;

34
00:03:39,602 --> 00:03:42,461
He's ecstasy personified.

35
00:03:42,461 --> 00:03:47,596
But who can extract the nectar?

36
00:03:47,728 --> 00:03:51,528
... need nectar extraction.

37
00:03:51,592 --> 00:03:54,336
So many things are like that,
they have some ...

38
00:03:54,385 --> 00:03:57,934
there's a method for how to extract.

39
00:03:58,019 --> 00:04:10,421
The method to extract the nectar of Kṛṣṇa
is sevā, self-giving, self-offering.

